              "number": 5,
              "question": "How are you going to treat your #1 diagnosis?",
              "answer": "\u25cf Eyelid scrubs bid.\n\u25cf Warm compresses bid.\n\u25cf Erythromycin or bacitracin ointment qhs\n\u25cf Unresponsive: Doxycycline 100mg PO bid\no Avoid in pregnant women, nursing mothers, children < 8 yrs\no Counsel regarding photosensitivity\n\u25cf Associated dry eyes: preservative free artificial tears 4-8 times/day\n\u25cf Short-term, low dose topical steroids for sterile corneal infiltrates or phlyctenulosis\n\u25cf Rosacea: Facial lesions treated with metronidazole gel 0.75% BID",
