              "answer": "\u25cf Warm compresses for 10min qid with light massage over lesion.\n\u25cf If lesion draining or associated with blepharitis: erythromycin or bacitracin ointment bid.\n\u25cf Doxycycline 100mg bid if associated w/ blepharitis/MGD\n\u25cf If chalazion fails to resolve after 3-4 weeks of appropriate medical therapy, incision and curettage vs. injection of steroid (if\nlesion near lacrimal apparatus).\no Steroid injection: risk of skin depigmentation, CRAO\n\u25cf Send recurrent or unusual chalazia to pathology",
