              "number": 6,
              "question": "What will you tell your patient about the natural history, prognosis and follow-up for treatment?",
              "answer": "Good prognosis. Lesion usually resolves over weeks to months when the contents drain either externally through eyelid skin or\ninternally through tarsus. Small amount of scar tissue may remain. Treating underlying blepharitis and MGD will decrease\nrecurrences.",
