              "answer": "\u25cf Topical abx (polytrim or fluoroquinolone gtts QID) x 5-7days\n\u25cf If H.influenzae, treat with oral augmentin (associated otitis, pneumonia, and meningitis)\n\u25cf If gonococcal, Ceftriaxone 1g IM x1. If corneal involvement is present, needs CTX 1g IV q12-24hrs\no add topical fluoroquinolone\no saline irrigation QID until discharge resolves\no add azithromycin x1 or doxy for 1 week to cover chlamydia",
              "keyPoints": [
                "Topical abx (polytrim or fluoroquinolone gtts QID) x 5-7days",
                "If H.influenzae, treat with oral augmentin (associated otitis, pneumonia, and meningitis)",
                "If gonococcal, Ceftriaxone 1g IM x1. If corneal involvement is present, needs CTX 1g IV q12-24hrs"
              ],
              "scoringKeywords": [
                "If H.influenzae, treat with oral augmentin",
                "Topical abx"
              ]
            },
            {
              "number": 6,
              "question": "What will you tell your patient about the natural history, prognosis and follow-up for treatment?",
              "answer": "Must use antibiotics, and close follow-up is needed to tailor treatment according to culture/sensitivity results. Improvement should\noccur within first few days, and resolution should occur within 1 week. Pt needs f/u every 2-3 days initially, then every 5-7 days until\nresolved. If severe, needs daily follow-up.\nIf +gonococcal conjunctivitis, patient and sexual partners should be evaluated for other STIs.",
              "keyPoints": [],
              "scoringKeywords": []
            }
          ],
          "diagnosisTitle": "Bacterial conjunctivitis"
        },
