                "Close any wound leaks",
                "Topical corticosteroids, cycloplegics"
              ]
            },
            {
              "number": 6,
              "question": "What will you tell your patient about the natural history, prognosis and follow-up for treatment?",
              "answer": "Choroidal detachment usually resolves with conservative management. Visual prognosis is good without suprachoroidal hemorrhage.\nPatient will require close follow-up (2-3 days) until choroidal detachment resolves sooner if significant hypotony or s/p surgical\nmanagement.",
