              "answer": "Optic nerve drusen slowly enlarge over time which can lead to compression of nerve fibers and visual field defects. The blood vessels\ncan also be compressed, leading to vascular occlusion and hemorrhage(very rare). Follow with annual HVF, photos, IOP check and\nmonitor for glaucoma",
              "keyPoints": [],
              "scoringKeywords": []
            }
          ],
          "diagnosisTitle": "Optic nerve head drusen"
