              "question": "What will you tell your patient about the natural history, prognosis and follow-up for treatment?",
              "answer": "Reassure parents that there is no eye turn and appearance of esotropia will resolve as face and nasal bridge grow. Parents should be\ncautioned that children with pseudostrabismus, like any child, can develop true strabismus later in life. Therefore, if any change in\nappearance occurs, a repeat evaluation may be warranted.",
              "keyPoints": [],
              "scoringKeywords": []
            }
          ],
          "diagnosisTitle": "Pseudostrabismus"
        },
