              "answer": "Refraction: previously over-minused refraction\nTear film: Dry eye syndrome\nFlattening of cornea: chronic CL wear, overcorrection from refractive surgery, progression of effect of RK\nLens: aphakia, lens dislocation, Dm\nWeak accommodation\n\u25cf Adie\u2019s tonic pupil\n\u25cf Third nerve palsy\n\u25cf Trauma\n\u25cf Drugs (chloroquine, phenothiazines, antihistamines, benzodiazepines, marijuana)\nRetina pushed forward\n\u25cf Central serous retinopathy, diabetic macular edema\n\u25cf Choroidal tumor (melanoma or hemangioma)\n\u25cf Orbital mass with pressure on posterior globe",
