              "answer": "Near aids\n\u25aa High-add bifocals \u25aa CCTV\n\u25aa High power single vision lens \u25aa Large print computer display, calculators, books.\n\u25aa Magnifiers: hand held, stand, electronic\n\u25aa Loupes\n\u25aa Talking books, watches, computer programs.\nDistance aids\n\u25aa Telescope\n\u25aa Absorptive lenses \u2013 for glare control in presence of media opacities or albinism\n\u25aa Night vision telescopes \u2013 for poor night vision e.g. retinitis pigmentosa.\nOther: Vocational and occupational counseling, canes, seeing eye dogs",
